The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Adhunik Metaliks Ltd has registered a 21.86 per cent growth in net sales at Rs 208.12 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 170.78 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The profit after tax rose 14.2 per cent to Rs 17.75 crore from Rs.15.54 crore a year ago.

 Jai Balaji Industries has posted net sales of 250 crore for the quarter ended June 30, 2007. The profit after tax was at Rs 23.59 crore, while the profit before tax was at Rs 35.78 crore. The earnings per share stood at Rs 5.01. 

 Gontermann-Peipers (India) Ltd has posted a net profit of Rs 3.77 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal against Rs 1 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The companys net turnover was Rs 45.45 crore compared with Rs 26.84 crore a year ago. 

 Gujarat NRE Cokes profit after tax was Rs 42.82 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 9.69 crore in the same quarter of the previous year. Profit before tax was Rs 50.21 crore. Income from operations rose to Rs 148.89 crore from Rs 64.76 crore.

 Subhash Projects and Marketing Ltd (SPML) has clocked a net profit of Rs 13.74 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 11.49 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. The companys revenues jumped to Rs 237.98 crore from Rs 111.68 crore a year ago.

 Ratnabali Capital Markets Ltd has recorded a profit after tax of Rs 5.36 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 5.65 crore in the same period of the previous fiscal. Income from operations was Rs 206.43 crore.

 Durgapur Steel Plant has registered a 70 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 220 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal. It recorded a 29 per cent increase in turnover at Rs 1,009 crore for the quarter.

 Ramsarup Industries has reported a 183 per cent rise in export sales at Rs 29.7 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 10.51 crore for the same period last year. The total income was at Rs 354.73 crore against Rs 312.21 crore in the year-ago period. 

 Balasore Alloys Ltd has registered a profit after tax of Rs 5.39 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 1.53 crore a year ago. The turnover increased to Rs 95.37 crore from Rs 64.82 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

 Stone India Ltd has recorded a net profit of Rs 3.78 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 3.14 crore a year ago.

